# 
# - Consumption enters as log(consumption_index); responses are cumulative
#   log deviations from t-1, directly comparable across horizons.
# - Balanced panel: 27 states x 48 months (2016.01 - 2019.12) with no gaps,
#   since the H2M covariates were dropped (they were the binding missingness
#   constraint in the previous spec, which left only 22 usable months).
# - Pooled regression uses state + month + year fixed effects; SEs clustered
#   by uf_code. Per-state regressions use Newey-West HAC with bandwidth
#   max(1, h) at horizon h.


# Pooled local projection setup
#
# Model at each horizon h in {0, ..., 12}:
#   y_{i,t+h} - y_{i,t-1} = beta_h * mp_shock_{i,t}
#                         + gamma_h' X_{i,t}
#                         + alpha_i + delta_m + tau_y + eps_{i,t+h}
#
# where y_{i,t} = log(consumption_index_{i,t}),
#       X_{i,t} includes lag_log_c, lag_mp_shock,
#       standard errors are clustered by state (uf_code).
#

# State by state local projection setup
# For each state s, estimate:
#   y_{s,t+h} - y_{s,t-1} = beta_{s,h} * mp_shock_{s,t}
#                         + gamma_{s,h}' X_{s,t}
#                         + delta_m + tau_y + u_{s,t+h}
# with HAC (Newey-West) standard errors within each state time series.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------